{
  "id": "RAW_84f6a1a2",
  "title": "测试 “Bash 是否就是你所需的一切” - Vercel",
  "url": "https://vercel.com/blog/testing-if-bash-is-all-you-need",
  "date": "2026-01-22 13:00:00",
  "author": "Ankur Goyal, Andrew Qu",
  "siteName": "Vercel News",
  "content": "<html>\n <head></head>\n <body>\n  <div data-customer-story=\"false\" class=\"flex flex-col items-center justify-start gap-6 flex-initial article-module__9eLiuW__content\">\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\"><i>We invited </i><a href=\"https://x.com/ankrgyl\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-track=\"true\" data-track-click-name=\"article_link\" data-track-click-value=\"https://x.com/ankrgyl\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight [&amp;_u]:no-underline\"><i>Ankur Goyal</i></a><i> from </i><a href=\"https://www.braintrust.dev/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-track=\"true\" data-track-click-name=\"article_link\" data-track-click-value=\"https://www.braintrust.dev/\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight [&amp;_u]:no-underline\"><i>Braintrust</i></a><i> to share how they tested the \"bash is all you need\" hypothesis for AI agents.</i></p>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">There's a growing conviction in the AI community that filesystems and bash are the optimal abstraction for AI agents. The logic makes sense: LLMs have been extensively trained on code, terminals, and file navigation, so you should be able to give your agent a shell and let it work.</p>\n   <div class=\"flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-4 max-w-none not-frist:mt-20 not-first:mb-10 mx-0 max-[600px]:max-w-none max-[600px]:px-7 max-[600px]:[li_&amp;]:pr-14 max-[600px]:[li_&amp;]:pl-0 max-[600px]:w-full max-[600px]:mt-12 max-[600px]:mb-6\">\n    <div class=\"rounded-[6px] p-2 bg-background-100 shadow-sm bg-clip-padding max-w-[900px] grid grid-cols-1 sm:border-l-0 sm:border-r-0 sm:rounded-none sm:border-[var(--guide-color)] sm:max-w-none sm:w-full\">\n     <img data-version=\"v1\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"900\" height=\"517\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"image-module__ssnYEW__intrinsic blog-mode-dependent-media-module__HJT-FW__addPadding image-module__ssnYEW__lightMode\" style=\"color:transparent\" srcset=\"https://vercel.com/vc-ap-vercel-marketing/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fassets.vercel.com%2Fimage%2Fupload%2Fcontentful%2Fimage%2Fe5382hct74si%2F77tgHuQZRMKfAug1XukPtp%2Fb986ec8f886ade68d4c01451e8d2adbd%2FScreenshot_2026-01-22_at_2.35.41%C3%A2__PM.png&amp;w=1080&amp;q=75 1x, https://vercel.com/vc-ap-vercel-marketing/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fassets.vercel.com%2Fimage%2Fupload%2Fcontentful%2Fimage%2Fe5382hct74si%2F77tgHuQZRMKfAug1XukPtp%2Fb986ec8f886ade68d4c01451e8d2adbd%2FScreenshot_2026-01-22_at_2.35.41%C3%A2__PM.png&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"https://vercel.com/vc-ap-vercel-marketing/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fassets.vercel.com%2Fimage%2Fupload%2Fcontentful%2Fimage%2Fe5382hct74si%2F77tgHuQZRMKfAug1XukPtp%2Fb986ec8f886ade68d4c01451e8d2adbd%2FScreenshot_2026-01-22_at_2.35.41%C3%A2__PM.png&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75\"><img data-version=\"v1\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"900\" height=\"517\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"image-module__ssnYEW__intrinsic blog-mode-dependent-media-module__HJT-FW__addPadding image-module__ssnYEW__darkMode\" style=\"color:transparent\" srcset=\"https://vercel.com/vc-ap-vercel-marketing/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fassets.vercel.com%2Fimage%2Fupload%2Fcontentful%2Fimage%2Fe5382hct74si%2F66FznbCzdqRNQwhBzVcOzm%2Fdc28c6cf8b0846e0336903d8470e958d%2FScreenshot_2026-01-22_at_2.35.18%C3%A2__PM.png&amp;w=1080&amp;q=75 1x, https://vercel.com/vc-ap-vercel-marketing/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fassets.vercel.com%2Fimage%2Fupload%2Fcontentful%2Fimage%2Fe5382hct74si%2F66FznbCzdqRNQwhBzVcOzm%2Fdc28c6cf8b0846e0336903d8470e958d%2FScreenshot_2026-01-22_at_2.35.18%C3%A2__PM.png&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"https://vercel.com/vc-ap-vercel-marketing/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fassets.vercel.com%2Fimage%2Fupload%2Fcontentful%2Fimage%2Fe5382hct74si%2F66FznbCzdqRNQwhBzVcOzm%2Fdc28c6cf8b0846e0336903d8470e958d%2FScreenshot_2026-01-22_at_2.35.18%C3%A2__PM.png&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75\">\n    </div>\n   </div>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">Even non-coding agents may benefit from this approach. Vercel's recent post on <a target=\"_self\" data-track=\"true\" data-track-click-name=\"article_link\" data-track-click-value=\"https://vercel.com/blog/how-to-build-agents-with-filesystems-and-bash\" data-zone=\"same\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight [&amp;_u]:no-underline\" href=\"https://vercel.com/blog/how-to-build-agents-with-filesystems-and-bash\">building agents with filesystems and bash</a> showed this by mapping sales calls, support tickets, and other structured data onto the filesystem. The agent greps for relevant sections, pulls what it needs, and builds context on demand.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">But there's an alternative view worth testing. Filesystems may be the right abstraction for exploring and retrieving context, but what about querying structured data? We <a href=\"https://github.com/braintrustdata/bash-agent-evals\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-track=\"true\" data-track-click-name=\"article_link\" data-track-click-value=\"https://github.com/braintrustdata/bash-agent-evals\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight [&amp;_u]:no-underline\">built an eval harness</a> to find out.</p>\n   <h2 class=\"text-heading-24 md:text-heading-32 font-semibold pt-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:pt-6 [#changelog-description_&amp;:first-child]:pt-0 w-full group relative text-module__fl7lUq__subheading\"><a class=\"flex items-center justify-center flex-col absolute left-0 bottom-0 mt-auto mb-auto w-8 h-8 rounded-full opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 -translate-x-3/4 group-hover:-translate-x-full delay-75 duration-300 transition-all text-gray-900 hover:text-gray-1000 hover:scale-110 focus-visible:-translate-x-full focus-visible:opacity-100 top-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:hidden\" href=\"#setting-up-the-eval\" id=\"setting-up-the-eval\" style=\"scroll-margin-top:90px\"> \n     <svg data-testid=\"geist-icon\" height=\"16\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"color:currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\">\n      <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path>\n     </svg> \n     <span class=\"sr-only\">Link to heading</span> \n    </a>Setting up the eval</h2>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">We tasked agents with querying a dataset of GitHub issues and pull requests. This type of semi-structured data mirrors real-world use cases like customer support tickets or sales call transcripts.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">Question complexity ranged from:</p>\n   <ul class=\"text-module__fl7lUq__unorderedList\">\n    <li class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph text-module__fl7lUq__listItem\">\n     <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">Simple queries: \"How many open issues mention 'security'?\"</p>\n    </li>\n    <li class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph text-module__fl7lUq__listItem\">\n     <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">Complex queries: \"Find issues where someone reported a bug and later someone submitted a pull request claiming to fix it\"</p>\n    </li>\n   </ul>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">Three agent approaches competed:</p>\n   <ol class=\"text-module__fl7lUq__orderedList\">\n    <li class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph text-module__fl7lUq__listItem\">\n     <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\"><b>SQL agent</b>: Direct database queries against a SQLite database containing the same data</p>\n    </li>\n    <li class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph text-module__fl7lUq__listItem\">\n     <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\"><b>Bash agent</b>: Using <a href=\"https://github.com/vercel-labs/bash-tool\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-track=\"true\" data-track-click-name=\"article_link\" data-track-click-value=\"https://github.com/vercel-labs/bash-tool\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight [&amp;_u]:no-underline\"><code>just-bash</code></a> to navigate and query JSON files on the filesystem</p>\n    </li>\n    <li class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph text-module__fl7lUq__listItem\">\n     <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\"><b>Filesystem agent</b>: Basic file tools (search, read) without full shell access</p>\n    </li>\n   </ol>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">Each agent received the same questions and was scored on accuracy.</p>\n   <h2 class=\"text-heading-24 md:text-heading-32 font-semibold pt-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:pt-6 [#changelog-description_&amp;:first-child]:pt-0 w-full group relative text-module__fl7lUq__subheading\"><a class=\"flex items-center justify-center flex-col absolute left-0 bottom-0 mt-auto mb-auto w-8 h-8 rounded-full opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 -translate-x-3/4 group-hover:-translate-x-full delay-75 duration-300 transition-all text-gray-900 hover:text-gray-1000 hover:scale-110 focus-visible:-translate-x-full focus-visible:opacity-100 top-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:hidden\" href=\"#initial-results\" id=\"initial-results\" style=\"scroll-margin-top:90px\"> \n     <svg data-testid=\"geist-icon\" height=\"16\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"color:currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\">\n      <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path>\n     </svg> \n     <span class=\"sr-only\">Link to heading</span> \n    </a>Initial results</h2>\n   <div class=\"scroller-module__6hSglq__overlayContainer text-module__fl7lUq__tableScroller scroller-module__6hSglq__isHorizontal\" data-geist-scroller=\"\" data-version=\"v1\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%\">\n    <div class=\"scroller-module__6hSglq__scroller text-module__fl7lUq__scrollerContainer\" data-geist-scroller-container=\"\" data-overflow=\"x\">\n     <div class=\"\">\n      <table class=\"text-module__fl7lUq__table\">\n       <tbody>\n        <tr>\n         <th>\n          <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\"><b>Agent</b></p>\n         </th>\n         <th>\n          <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\"><b>Accuracy</b></p>\n         </th>\n         <th>\n          <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\"><b>Avg Tokens</b></p>\n         </th>\n         <th>\n          <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\"><b>Cost</b></p>\n         </th>\n         <th>\n          <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\"><b>Duration</b></p>\n         </th>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n         <td>\n          <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">SQL</p>\n         </td>\n         <td>\n          <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">100%</p>\n         </td>\n         <td>\n          <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">155,531</p>\n         </td>\n         <td>\n          <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">$0.51</p>\n         </td>\n         <td>\n          <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">45s</p>\n         </td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n         <td>\n          <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">Bash</p>\n         </td>\n         <td>\n          <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">52.7%</p>\n         </td>\n         <td>\n          <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">1,062,031</p>\n         </td>\n         <td>\n          <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">$3.34</p>\n         </td>\n         <td>\n          <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">401s</p>\n         </td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n         <td>\n          <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">Filesystem</p>\n         </td>\n         <td>\n          <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">63.0%</p>\n         </td>\n         <td>\n          <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">1,275,871</p>\n         </td>\n         <td>\n          <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">$3.89</p>\n         </td>\n         <td>\n          <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">126s</p>\n         </td>\n        </tr>\n       </tbody>\n      </table>\n     </div>\n    </div>\n   </div>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">SQL dominated. It hit 100% accuracy while bash achieved just 53%. Bash also used 7x more tokens and cost 6.5x more, while taking 9x longer to run. Even basic filesystem tools (search, read) outperformed full bash access, hitting 63% accuracy.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">You can explore the <a href=\"https://www.braintrust.dev/app/braintrust-labs/p/bash-evals/experiments/sql-claude-sonnet-4-5?c=bash-claude-sonnet-4-5\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-track=\"true\" data-track-click-name=\"article_link\" data-track-click-value=\"https://www.braintrust.dev/app/braintrust-labs/p/bash-evals/experiments/sql-claude-sonnet-4-5?c=bash-claude-sonnet-4-5\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight [&amp;_u]:no-underline\">SQL experiment</a>, <a href=\"https://www.braintrust.dev/app/braintrust-labs/p/bash-evals/experiments/bash-claude-sonnet-4-5?c=sql-claude-sonnet-4-5\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-track=\"true\" data-track-click-name=\"article_link\" data-track-click-value=\"https://www.braintrust.dev/app/braintrust-labs/p/bash-evals/experiments/bash-claude-sonnet-4-5?c=sql-claude-sonnet-4-5\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight [&amp;_u]:no-underline\">bash experiment</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.braintrust.dev/app/braintrust-labs/p/bash-evals/experiments/fs-claude-sonnet-4-5?c=bash-sqlite-claude-sonnet-4-5\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-track=\"true\" data-track-click-name=\"article_link\" data-track-click-value=\"https://www.braintrust.dev/app/braintrust-labs/p/bash-evals/experiments/fs-claude-sonnet-4-5?c=bash-sqlite-claude-sonnet-4-5\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight [&amp;_u]:no-underline\">filesystem experiment</a> results directly.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">One surprising finding was that the bash agent generated <a href=\"https://www.braintrust.dev/app/braintrust-labs/p/bash-evals/experiments/bash-claude-opus-4-5?c=fs-claude-opus-4-5&amp;tvt=trace&amp;r=5507f609-6877-4432-bb20-9b7811cdd90b&amp;s=934fe28f-c04d-4f28-8e4e-7b69725b1495&amp;st=input&amp;fs=1\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-track=\"true\" data-track-click-name=\"article_link\" data-track-click-value=\"https://www.braintrust.dev/app/braintrust-labs/p/bash-evals/experiments/bash-claude-opus-4-5?c=fs-claude-opus-4-5&amp;tvt=trace&amp;r=5507f609-6877-4432-bb20-9b7811cdd90b&amp;s=934fe28f-c04d-4f28-8e4e-7b69725b1495&amp;st=input&amp;fs=1\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight [&amp;_u]:no-underline\">highly sophisticated shell commands</a>, chaining <code>find</code>, <code>grep</code>, <code>jq</code>, <code>awk</code>, and <code>xargs</code> in ways that rarely appear in typical agent workflows. The model clearly has deep knowledge of shell scripting, but that knowledge didn't translate to better task performance.</p>\n   <div class=\"flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-4 max-w-none not-frist:mt-20 not-first:mb-10 mx-0 max-[600px]:max-w-none max-[600px]:px-7 max-[600px]:[li_&amp;]:pr-14 max-[600px]:[li_&amp;]:pl-0 max-[600px]:w-full max-[600px]:mt-12 max-[600px]:mb-6\">\n    <div class=\"rounded-[6px] p-2 bg-background-100 shadow-sm bg-clip-padding max-w-[900px] grid grid-cols-1 sm:border-l-0 sm:border-r-0 sm:rounded-none sm:border-[var(--guide-color)] sm:max-w-none sm:w-full\">\n     <img data-version=\"v1\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"900\" height=\"619\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"image-module__ssnYEW__intrinsic blog-mode-dependent-media-module__HJT-FW__addPadding\" style=\"color:transparent\" srcset=\"https://vercel.com/vc-ap-vercel-marketing/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fassets.vercel.com%2Fimage%2Fupload%2Fcontentful%2Fimage%2Fe5382hct74si%2F6Cvx8yBqPQE8BrsQMAK26c%2Fc280298be058861f971726019c072146%2Fgrep-chain.png&amp;w=1080&amp;q=75 1x, https://vercel.com/vc-ap-vercel-marketing/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fassets.vercel.com%2Fimage%2Fupload%2Fcontentful%2Fimage%2Fe5382hct74si%2F6Cvx8yBqPQE8BrsQMAK26c%2Fc280298be058861f971726019c072146%2Fgrep-chain.png&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"https://vercel.com/vc-ap-vercel-marketing/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fassets.vercel.com%2Fimage%2Fupload%2Fcontentful%2Fimage%2Fe5382hct74si%2F6Cvx8yBqPQE8BrsQMAK26c%2Fc280298be058861f971726019c072146%2Fgrep-chain.png&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75\">\n    </div>\n   </div>\n   <h2 class=\"text-heading-24 md:text-heading-32 font-semibold pt-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:pt-6 [#changelog-description_&amp;:first-child]:pt-0 w-full group relative text-module__fl7lUq__subheading\"><a class=\"flex items-center justify-center flex-col absolute left-0 bottom-0 mt-auto mb-auto w-8 h-8 rounded-full opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 -translate-x-3/4 group-hover:-translate-x-full delay-75 duration-300 transition-all text-gray-900 hover:text-gray-1000 hover:scale-110 focus-visible:-translate-x-full focus-visible:opacity-100 top-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:hidden\" href=\"#debugging-the-results\" id=\"debugging-the-results\" style=\"scroll-margin-top:90px\"> \n     <svg data-testid=\"geist-icon\" height=\"16\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"color:currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\">\n      <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path>\n     </svg> \n     <span class=\"sr-only\">Link to heading</span> \n    </a>Debugging the results</h2>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">The eval revealed substantive issues requiring attention.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\"><b>Performance bottlenecks.</b> Commands that should run in milliseconds were timing out at 10 seconds. <code>stat()</code> calls across 68,000 files were the culprit. The <a href=\"https://x.com/cramforce/status/2010516747070349709\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-track=\"true\" data-track-click-name=\"article_link\" data-track-click-value=\"https://x.com/cramforce/status/2010516747070349709\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight [&amp;_u]:no-underline\"><code>just-bash</code> tool received optimizations</a> addressing this.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\"><b>Missing schema context.</b> The bash agent didn't know the structure of the JSON files it was querying. Adding schema information and example commands to the system prompt helped, but not enough to close the gap.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\"><b>Eval scoring issues.</b> Hand-checking failed cases revealed several questions where the \"expected\" answer was actually wrong, or where the agent found additional valid results that the scorer penalized. Five questions received corrections addressing ambiguities or dataset mismatches.</p>\n   <ul class=\"text-module__fl7lUq__unorderedList\">\n    <li class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph text-module__fl7lUq__listItem\">\n     <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">\"Which repositories have the most unique issue reporters\" was ambiguous between org-level and repo-level grouping</p>\n    </li>\n    <li class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph text-module__fl7lUq__listItem\">\n     <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">Several questions had expected outputs that didn't match the actual dataset</p>\n    </li>\n    <li class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph text-module__fl7lUq__listItem\">\n     <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">The bash agent sometimes found more valid results than the reference answers included</p>\n    </li>\n   </ul>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">The Vercel team submitted a <a href=\"https://github.com/braintrustdata/bash-agent-evals/pull/5\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-track=\"true\" data-track-click-name=\"article_link\" data-track-click-value=\"https://github.com/braintrustdata/bash-agent-evals/pull/5\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight [&amp;_u]:no-underline\">PR with the corrections</a>.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">After fixes to both <code>just-bash</code> and the eval itself, the performance gap narrowed considerably.</p>\n   <h2 class=\"text-heading-24 md:text-heading-32 font-semibold pt-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:pt-6 [#changelog-description_&amp;:first-child]:pt-0 w-full group relative text-module__fl7lUq__subheading\"><a class=\"flex items-center justify-center flex-col absolute left-0 bottom-0 mt-auto mb-auto w-8 h-8 rounded-full opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 -translate-x-3/4 group-hover:-translate-x-full delay-75 duration-300 transition-all text-gray-900 hover:text-gray-1000 hover:scale-110 focus-visible:-translate-x-full focus-visible:opacity-100 top-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:hidden\" href=\"#the-hybrid-approach\" id=\"the-hybrid-approach\" style=\"scroll-margin-top:90px\"> \n     <svg data-testid=\"geist-icon\" height=\"16\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"color:currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\">\n      <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path>\n     </svg> \n     <span class=\"sr-only\">Link to heading</span> \n    </a>The hybrid approach</h2>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">Then we tried a different idea. Instead of choosing one abstraction, give the agent both:</p>\n   <ul class=\"text-module__fl7lUq__unorderedList\">\n    <li class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph text-module__fl7lUq__listItem\">\n     <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">Let it use bash to explore and manipulate files</p>\n    </li>\n    <li class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph text-module__fl7lUq__listItem\">\n     <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">Also provide access to a SQLite database when that's the right tool</p>\n    </li>\n   </ul>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">The hybrid agent developed an interesting behavior. It would run SQL queries, then verify results by grepping through the filesystem. This double-checking is why the hybrid approach consistently hits 100% accuracy, while pure SQL occasionally gets things wrong.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">You can explore the <a href=\"https://www.braintrust.dev/app/braintrust-labs/p/bash-evals/experiments/bash-sqlite-claude-opus-4-5?c=bash-claude-opus-4-5\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-track=\"true\" data-track-click-name=\"article_link\" data-track-click-value=\"https://www.braintrust.dev/app/braintrust-labs/p/bash-evals/experiments/bash-sqlite-claude-opus-4-5?c=bash-claude-opus-4-5\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight [&amp;_u]:no-underline\">hybrid experiment results</a> directly.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">The tradeoff is cost. The hybrid approach uses roughly two times as many tokens as pure SQL, since it reasons about tool choice and verifies its work.</p>\n   <h2 class=\"text-heading-24 md:text-heading-32 font-semibold pt-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:pt-6 [#changelog-description_&amp;:first-child]:pt-0 w-full group relative text-module__fl7lUq__subheading\"><a class=\"flex items-center justify-center flex-col absolute left-0 bottom-0 mt-auto mb-auto w-8 h-8 rounded-full opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 -translate-x-3/4 group-hover:-translate-x-full delay-75 duration-300 transition-all text-gray-900 hover:text-gray-1000 hover:scale-110 focus-visible:-translate-x-full focus-visible:opacity-100 top-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:hidden\" href=\"#key-learnings\" id=\"key-learnings\" style=\"scroll-margin-top:90px\"> \n     <svg data-testid=\"geist-icon\" height=\"16\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"color:currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\">\n      <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path>\n     </svg> \n     <span class=\"sr-only\">Link to heading</span> \n    </a>Key learnings</h2>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">After all the fixes to <code>just-bash</code>, the eval dataset, and data loading issues, bash-sqlite emerged as the most reliable approach. The \"winner\" wasn't raw accuracy on a single run, but consistent accuracy through self-verification.</p>\n   <div class=\"flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-4 max-w-none not-frist:mt-20 not-first:mb-10 mx-0 max-[600px]:max-w-none max-[600px]:px-7 max-[600px]:[li_&amp;]:pr-14 max-[600px]:[li_&amp;]:pl-0 max-[600px]:w-full max-[600px]:mt-12 max-[600px]:mb-6\">\n    <div class=\"rounded-[6px] p-2 bg-background-100 shadow-sm bg-clip-padding max-w-[900px] grid grid-cols-1 sm:border-l-0 sm:border-r-0 sm:rounded-none sm:border-[var(--guide-color)] sm:max-w-none sm:w-full\">\n     <img data-version=\"v1\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"900\" height=\"417\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"1\" class=\"image-module__ssnYEW__intrinsic blog-mode-dependent-media-module__HJT-FW__addPadding\" style=\"color:transparent\" srcset=\"https://vercel.com/vc-ap-vercel-marketing/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fassets.vercel.com%2Fimage%2Fupload%2Fcontentful%2Fimage%2Fe5382hct74si%2F7KgOPR8IraRs4nYwxM52Ef%2F13e193cb6e596c02121374d1cf8d7f9c%2Fall-experiments.png&amp;w=1080&amp;q=75 1x, https://vercel.com/vc-ap-vercel-marketing/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fassets.vercel.com%2Fimage%2Fupload%2Fcontentful%2Fimage%2Fe5382hct74si%2F7KgOPR8IraRs4nYwxM52Ef%2F13e193cb6e596c02121374d1cf8d7f9c%2Fall-experiments.png&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 2x\" src=\"https://vercel.com/vc-ap-vercel-marketing/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fassets.vercel.com%2Fimage%2Fupload%2Fcontentful%2Fimage%2Fe5382hct74si%2F7KgOPR8IraRs4nYwxM52Ef%2F13e193cb6e596c02121374d1cf8d7f9c%2Fall-experiments.png&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75\">\n    </div>\n   </div>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">Over 200 messages and hundreds of traces later, we had:</p>\n   <ul class=\"text-module__fl7lUq__unorderedList\">\n    <li class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph text-module__fl7lUq__listItem\">\n     <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">Fixed performance bottlenecks in <code>just-bash</code></p>\n    </li>\n    <li class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph text-module__fl7lUq__listItem\">\n     <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">Corrected five ambiguous or wrong expected answers in the eval</p>\n    </li>\n    <li class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph text-module__fl7lUq__listItem\">\n     <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">Found a data loading bug that caused off-by-one errors</p>\n    </li>\n    <li class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph text-module__fl7lUq__listItem\">\n     <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">Watched agents develop sophisticated verification strategies</p>\n    </li>\n   </ul>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">The bash agent's tendency to check its own work turned out to be valuable just not for accuracy, but also for surfacing problems that would have gone unnoticed with a pure SQL approach.</p>\n   <h2 class=\"text-heading-24 md:text-heading-32 font-semibold pt-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:pt-6 [#changelog-description_&amp;:first-child]:pt-0 w-full group relative text-module__fl7lUq__subheading\"><a class=\"flex items-center justify-center flex-col absolute left-0 bottom-0 mt-auto mb-auto w-8 h-8 rounded-full opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 -translate-x-3/4 group-hover:-translate-x-full delay-75 duration-300 transition-all text-gray-900 hover:text-gray-1000 hover:scale-110 focus-visible:-translate-x-full focus-visible:opacity-100 top-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:hidden\" href=\"#what-this-means-for-agent-design\" id=\"what-this-means-for-agent-design\" style=\"scroll-margin-top:90px\"> \n     <svg data-testid=\"geist-icon\" height=\"16\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"color:currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\">\n      <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path>\n     </svg> \n     <span class=\"sr-only\">Link to heading</span> \n    </a>What this means for agent design</h2>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">For structured data with clear schemas, SQL remains the most direct path. It's fast, well-understood, and uses fewer tokens.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">For exploration and verification, bash provides flexibility that SQL can't match. Agents can inspect files, spot-check results, and catch edge cases through filesystem access.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">But the bigger lesson is about evals themselves. The back-and-forth between Braintrust and the Vercel team, with detailed traces at every step, is what actually improved the tools and the benchmark. Without that visibility, we'd still be debating which abstraction \"won\" based on flawed data.</p>\n   <h2 class=\"text-heading-24 md:text-heading-32 font-semibold pt-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:pt-6 [#changelog-description_&amp;:first-child]:pt-0 w-full group relative text-module__fl7lUq__subheading\"><a class=\"flex items-center justify-center flex-col absolute left-0 bottom-0 mt-auto mb-auto w-8 h-8 rounded-full opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 -translate-x-3/4 group-hover:-translate-x-full delay-75 duration-300 transition-all text-gray-900 hover:text-gray-1000 hover:scale-110 focus-visible:-translate-x-full focus-visible:opacity-100 top-[calc(var(--grid-divider-gap)/1.5)] [#changelog-description_&amp;]:hidden\" href=\"#run-your-own-benchmarks\" id=\"run-your-own-benchmarks\" style=\"scroll-margin-top:90px\"> \n     <svg data-testid=\"geist-icon\" height=\"16\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" style=\"color:currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\">\n      <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M8.46968 1.46968C10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 -0.203923 14.5303 1.46968C16.2039 3.14329 16.2039 5.85674 14.5303 7.53034L12.0303 10.0303L10.9697 8.96968L13.4697 6.46968C14.5575 5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 13.4697 2.53034C12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 1.44252 9.53034 2.53034L7.03034 5.03034L5.96968 3.96968L8.46968 1.46968ZM11.5303 5.53034L5.53034 11.5303L4.46968 10.4697L10.4697 4.46968L11.5303 5.53034ZM1.46968 14.5303C3.14329 16.2039 5.85673 16.204 7.53034 14.5303L10.0303 12.0303L8.96968 10.9697L6.46968 13.4697C5.38186 14.5575 3.61816 14.5575 2.53034 13.4697C1.44252 12.3819 1.44252 10.6182 2.53034 9.53034L5.03034 7.03034L3.96968 5.96968L1.46968 8.46968C-0.203923 10.1433 -0.203925 12.8567 1.46968 14.5303Z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path>\n     </svg> \n     <span class=\"sr-only\">Link to heading</span> \n    </a>Run your own benchmarks</h2>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">The <a href=\"https://github.com/braintrustdata/bash-agent-evals\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-track=\"true\" data-track-click-name=\"article_link\" data-track-click-value=\"https://github.com/braintrustdata/bash-agent-evals\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight [&amp;_u]:no-underline\">eval harness is open source</a>.</p>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">You can swap in your own:</p>\n   <ul class=\"text-module__fl7lUq__unorderedList\">\n    <li class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph text-module__fl7lUq__listItem\">\n     <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">Dataset (customer tickets, sales calls, logs, whatever you're working with)</p>\n    </li>\n    <li class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph text-module__fl7lUq__listItem\">\n     <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">Agent implementations</p>\n    </li>\n    <li class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph text-module__fl7lUq__listItem\">\n     <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\">Questions that matter to your use case</p>\n    </li>\n   </ul>\n   <p class=\"text-copy-16 lg:text-copy-18 text-module__fl7lUq__paragraph\"><i>This post was written by </i><a href=\"https://x.com/ankrgyl\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-track=\"true\" data-track-click-name=\"article_link\" data-track-click-value=\"https://x.com/ankrgyl\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight [&amp;_u]:no-underline\"><i>Ankur Goyal</i></a><i> and the team at </i><a href=\"https://www.braintrust.dev/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-track=\"true\" data-track-click-name=\"article_link\" data-track-click-value=\"https://www.braintrust.dev/\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight [&amp;_u]:no-underline\"><i>Braintrust</i></a><i>, who build evaluation infrastructure for AI applications. The eval harness is open source and integrates with </i><a href=\"https://github.com/vercel-labs/bash-tool\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-track=\"true\" data-track-click-name=\"article_link\" data-track-click-value=\"https://github.com/vercel-labs/bash-tool\" data-zone=\"null\" class=\"link-module__Q1NRQq__link link-module__Q1NRQq__highlight [&amp;_u]:no-underline\"><code><i>just-bash</i></code></a><i> from Vercel.</i></p>\n  </div>\n </body>\n</html>",
  "aiSummary": "本文评估了 AI 智能体领域中 “Bash 就是你所需的一切” 这一假设，结论是 SQL-Bash 混合方法在准确性和自我验证方面达到了最佳平衡。",
  "oneSentenceSummary": "本文评估了 AI 智能体领域中 “Bash 就是你所需的一切” 这一假设，结论是 SQL-Bash 混合方法在准确性和自我验证方面达到了最佳平衡。",
  "summary": "文章详细介绍了 Braintrust 与 Vercel 之间的一项合作实验，旨在测试文件系统和 Bash 是否是 AI 智能体查询半结构化数据的最佳抽象。通过对比 SQL、Bash 和基础文件系统智能体，研究最初发现 SQL 在准确性、成本和速度上显著优于 Bash。然而，进一步的调试揭示了 Bash 工具的性能瓶颈以及评估数据集本身的缺陷。最终结果表明，虽然 SQL 在结构化查询方面表现卓越，但混合方法（允许智能体同时使用 SQL 进行数据检索和 Bash 进行探索与验证）通过智能体的自我纠错，实现了最高的可靠性和 100% 的准确率。",
  "mainPoints": [
    {
      "point": "在结构化数据任务中，SQL 智能体的表现显著优于纯 Bash 智能体。",
      "explanation": "初始评估显示，SQL 实现了 100% 的准确率，且成本比 Bash 低 6.5 倍，执行速度快 9 倍；而 Bash 在处理复杂的 JSON 查询和性能瓶颈方面表现挣扎。"
    },
    {
      "point": "SQL-Bash 混合方法通过自我验证提供了最高的可靠性。",
      "explanation": "配备这两种工具的智能体会利用 SQL 提高效率，同时利用 Bash 在文件系统中“复核”结果，从而捕捉到纯 SQL 可能会遗漏的边缘情况。"
    },
    {
      "point": "“评估调试”过程与基准测试结果本身同样至关重要。",
      "explanation": "详细的追踪显示，智能体得分较低通常是由工具性能问题、缺失 Schema 上下文、甚至是评估数据集“基准真相”中的错误导致的。"
    },
    {
      "point": "Bash 为探索提供了 SQL 无法比拟的灵活抽象。",
      "explanation": "虽然在计数或过滤方面效率较低，但 Bash 允许智能体导航非结构化数据、检查原始文件，并处理没有固定 Schema 的场景。"
    }
  ],
  "keyQuotes": [
    "模型显然对 Shell 脚本有很深的理解，但这种知识并没有转化为更好的任务表现。",
    "混合智能体表现出一种有趣的行为：它会运行 SQL 查询，然后通过在文件系统中执行 grep 来验证结果。",
    "“赢家”并非单次运行的原始准确率，而是通过自我验证实现的一致准确性。",
    "对于具有清晰 Schema 的结构化数据，SQL 仍然是最直接的路径。它速度快、易于理解且消耗更少的 Token。",
    "如果没有这种可见性，我们可能还在基于错误的数据争论哪种抽象更胜一筹。"
  ],
